  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Nowodworska's eldest daughter and her-- with her younger sister, who told us, me that, in fact, beginning of August, the Germans took all the inhabitants of the houses there as protection for the tanks, German tanks, advancing against Polish positions.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There were women, children, regardless.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my mother was among them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Fortunately, there were-- the Polish unit liberated them from the Germans, but she found herself in the old city, which was quite a way from where we were.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And where the, for a month, the fighting was absolutely ferocious.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So all they knew was that she had been there and that the last thing that happened, she had gone to the camp at Pruszkow as well.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But what had happened to her after that, again, no one knew.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
